Create a multimodule application that contains core and datasource modules.

In datasource module create a DataSourceConfigurationProperties that contains
datasource url, username, and password properties.
Create a configuration class in datasource module that configures the datasource bean.

Add datasource module as a dependency in the core module.

In core application.properties by using autocomplete fill in the datasource property values
In core module create a simple spring boot application that after context refreshed event
creates a users table if not exists and inserts one user having a random username.

note:
Use JDBC API to execute sql statements.
the datasource module configuration must be automatically detected by the core module